The paper focuses on image denoising using a convolutional neural network, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of discriminative learning methods (cs.LG) and the ability to handle spatially variant noise (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions benchmarking against BM3D, which is a popular image processing algorithm (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between inference speed and denoising performance, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
